nodes.description: A membrane that is one of the two lipid bilayers of an organelle envelope or the outermost membrane of single membrane bound organelle.

nodes.name: endoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the endoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.name: rough endoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the rough endoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.name: smooth endoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the smooth endoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.name: sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the sarcoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.name: junctional sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The part of the sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane that contains calcium release channels, is devoted to calcium release and is juxtaposed to transverse tubule membrane. The junctional sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane consists of the junctional region of the terminal cisterna membrane.

nodes.name: free sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The part of the sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane that contains calcium pumps and is devoted to calcium uptake. The free sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane consists of the longitudinal sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane and the non-junctional region of the terminal cisterna membrane.

nodes.name: endoplasmic reticulum tubular network membrane
nodes.description: The membrane of the endoplasmic reticulum tubular network.

nodes.name: vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any membrane-bounded vesicle in the cell.

nodes.name: cytoplasmic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a cytoplasmic vesicle.

nodes.name: inner acrosomal membrane
nodes.description: The acrosomal membrane region that underlies the acrosomal vesicle and is located toward the sperm nucleus. This region is responsible for molecular interactions allowing the sperm to penetrate the zona pellucida and fuses with the egg plasma membrane.

nodes.name: outer acrosomal membrane
nodes.description: The acrosomal membrane region that underlies the plasma membrane of the sperm. This membrane fuses with the sperm plasma membrane as part of the acrosome reaction.

nodes.name: endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an endosome.

nodes.name: early endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an early endosome.

nodes.name: postsynaptic early endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a postsynaptic early endosome.

nodes.name: late endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a late endosome.

nodes.name: multivesicular body membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a multivesicular body.

nodes.name: endolysosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an endolysosome. An endolysosome is a transient hybrid organelle formed by fusion of a late endosome with a lysosome.

nodes.name: recycling endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a recycling endosome.

nodes.name: postsynaptic endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a postsynaptic endosome.

nodes.name: postsynaptic early endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a postsynaptic early endosome.

nodes.name: postsynaptic recycling endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a postsynaptic recycling endosome.

nodes.name: presynaptic endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a presynaptic endosome.

nodes.name: macropinosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a macropinosome.

nodes.name: transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a transport vesicle.

nodes.name: ER to Golgi transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances from the endoplasmic reticulum to the Golgi.

nodes.name: Golgi to ER transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances from the Golgi to the ER.

nodes.name: inter-Golgi transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances within the Golgi.

nodes.name: trans-Golgi network transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances between the trans-Golgi network and other parts of the cell.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted acetylcholine transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted acetylcholine transport vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted glutamate transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted glutamate transport vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted monoamine transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted monoamine transport vesicle.

nodes.name: exocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an exocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: synaptic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a synaptic vesicle.

nodes.name: Golgi-associated vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle associated with the Golgi apparatus.

nodes.name: trans-Golgi network transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances between the trans-Golgi network and other parts of the cell.

nodes.name: COPI-coated vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a COPI-coated vesicle.

nodes.name: Golgi to ER transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances from the Golgi to the ER.

nodes.name: inter-Golgi transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances within the Golgi.

nodes.name: chitosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a chitosome.

nodes.name: coated vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a coated vesicle.

nodes.name: ER to Golgi transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances from the endoplasmic reticulum to the Golgi.

nodes.name: COPI-coated vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a COPI-coated vesicle.

nodes.name: Golgi to ER transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances from the Golgi to the ER.

nodes.name: inter-Golgi transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances within the Golgi.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated vesicle.

nodes.name: trans-Golgi network transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances between the trans-Golgi network and other parts of the cell.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated endocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated endocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted acetylcholine transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted acetylcholine transport vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted glutamate transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted glutamate transport vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted monoamine transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted monoamine transport vesicle.

nodes.name: endocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an endocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated endocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated endocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: phagocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a phagocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: early phagosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an early phagosome.

nodes.name: phagolysosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a phagolysosome.

nodes.name: peribacteroid membrane
nodes.description: A membrane that surrounds one or more bacteroids (such as nitrogen-fixing bacteroids within legume root nodule cells).

nodes.name: organellar chromatophore outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, of the two lipid bilayers surrounding an organellar chromatophore.

nodes.name: secretory granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a secretory granule.

nodes.name: acrosomal membrane
nodes.description: The membrane that surrounds the acrosomal lumen. The acrosome is a special type of lysosome in the head of a spermatozoon that contains acid hydrolases and is concerned with the breakdown of the outer membrane of the ovum during fertilization.

nodes.name: platelet dense granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the platelet dense granule.

nodes.name: platelet alpha granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the platelet alpha granule.

nodes.name: dense core granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a dense core granule.

nodes.name: neuronal dense core vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a neuronal dense core vesicle.

nodes.name: azurophil granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an azurophil granule, a primary lysosomal granule found in neutrophil granulocytes that contains a wide range of hydrolytic enzymes and is released into the extracellular fluid.

nodes.name: specific granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a specific granule, a granule with a membranous, tubular internal structure, found primarily in mature neutrophil cells. Most are released into the extracellular fluid. Specific granules contain lactoferrin, lysozyme, vitamin B12 binding protein and elastase.

nodes.name: chromaffin granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a chromaffin granule, a specialized secretory vesicle found in the cells of adrenal glands and various other organs, which is concerned with the synthesis, storage, metabolism, and secretion of epinephrine and norepinephrine.

nodes.name: zymogen granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a zymogen granule.

nodes.name: tertiary granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a tertiary granule.

nodes.name: lamellar body membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a lamellar body. A lamellar body is a membrane-bounded organelle, specialized for the storage and secretion of various substances (surfactant phospholipids, glycoproteins and acid phosphates) which are arranged in the form of tightly packed, concentric, membrane sheets or lamellae. Has some similar properties to, but is distinct from, a lysosome.

nodes.name: alveolar lamellar body membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an alveolar lamellar body, a specialized secretory organelle found in type II pneumocytes and involved in the synthesis, secretion, and reutilization of pulmonary surfactant.

nodes.name: epidermal lamellar body membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an epidermal lamellar body, a specialized secretory organelle found in keratinocytes and involved in the formation of an impermeable, lipid-containing membrane that serves as a water barrier and is required for correct skin barrier function.

nodes.name: ficolin-1-rich granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a ficolin-1-rich granule.

nodes.name: merozoite dense granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a dense granule of the type found in apicomplexan parasites.

nodes.name: contractile vacuolar membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the contractile vacuole.

nodes.name: aleurone grain membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an aleurone grain.

nodes.name: Cvt vesicle membrane
nodes.description: Either of the two lipid bilayers surrounding a Cvt vesicle, a vesicle that functions in the cytoplasm-to-vacuole targeting (Cvt) pathway.

nodes.name: esterosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an esterosome. This membrane has characteristics of rough endoplasmic reticulum (RER) membranes.

nodes.name: gut granule membrane
nodes.description: The membrane of a gut granule, a lysosome-related organelle contained within the intestinal cells of the nematode C. elegans.

nodes.name: organellar chromatophore membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround an organellar chromatophore.

nodes.name: organellar chromatophore inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, of the two lipid bilayers surrounding an organellar chromatophore.

nodes.name: organellar chromatophore outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, of the two lipid bilayers surrounding an organellar chromatophore.

nodes.name: organellar chromatophore thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer membrane of any thylakoid within an organellar chromatophore.

nodes.name: pigment granule membrane
nodes.description: Any membrane that is part of a pigment granule.

nodes.name: melanosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a melanosome.

nodes.name: multivesicular body, internal vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a multivesicular body internal vesicle.

nodes.name: phagolysosome vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bylayer surrounding a phagolysosome.

nodes.name: rod photoreceptor disc membrane
nodes.description: Stack of disc membranes located inside a rod photoreceptor outer segment, and containing densely packed molecules of rhodopsin photoreceptor proteins that traverse the lipid bilayer. It is thought that rod disc membranes arise as evaginations of the ciliary membrane near the base of the outer segment, which then become completely separated from the ciliary membrane, during the development of the rod outer segment.

nodes.name: organelle inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of an organelle envelope; usually highly selective to most ions and metabolites.

nodes.name: nuclear inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the nuclear envelope.

nodes.name: mitochondrial inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the mitochondrial envelope. It is highly folded to form cristae.

nodes.name: plastid inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the plastid envelope; also faces the plastid stroma.

nodes.name: chloroplast inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the chloroplast envelope; also faces the chloroplast stroma.

nodes.name: chromoplast inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the chromoplast envelope; also faces the chromoplast stroma.

nodes.name: amyloplast inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the amyloplast envelope; also faces the amyloplast stroma.

nodes.name: cyanelle inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the cyanelle envelope; also faces the cyanelle stroma.

nodes.name: nuclear membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround the nucleus and form the nuclear envelope; excludes the intermembrane space.

nodes.name: nuclear inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the nuclear envelope.

nodes.name: nuclear outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the nuclear envelope; continuous with the endoplasmic reticulum of the cell and sometimes studded with ribosomes.

nodes.name: mitochondrial membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround the mitochondrion and form the mitochondrial envelope.

nodes.name: mitochondrial outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the mitochondrial envelope.

nodes.name: mitochondrial inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the mitochondrial envelope. It is highly folded to form cristae.

nodes.name: Golgi cisterna membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the thin, flattened compartments that form the central portion of the Golgi complex.

nodes.name: Golgi cis cisterna membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the thin, flattened compartments that form the cis portion of the Golgi complex.

nodes.name: Golgi medial cisterna membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the thin, flattened compartments that form the medial portion of the Golgi complex.

nodes.name: Golgi trans cisterna membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the thin, flattened compartments that form the trans portion of the Golgi complex.

nodes.name: trans-Golgi network membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the compartments that make up the trans-Golgi network.

nodes.name: rhoptry membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a rhoptry.

nodes.name: plastid membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround a plastid and form the plastid envelope.

nodes.name: plastid outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the plastid envelope.

nodes.name: chloroplast outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the chloroplast envelope.

nodes.name: chromoplast outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the chromoplast envelope.

nodes.name: cyanelle outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the cyanelle envelope.

nodes.name: plastid inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the plastid envelope; also faces the plastid stroma.

nodes.name: chloroplast inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the chloroplast envelope; also faces the chloroplast stroma.

nodes.name: chromoplast inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the chromoplast envelope; also faces the chromoplast stroma.

nodes.name: amyloplast inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the amyloplast envelope; also faces the amyloplast stroma.

nodes.name: cyanelle inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the cyanelle envelope; also faces the cyanelle stroma.

nodes.name: chloroplast membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround a chloroplast and form the chloroplast envelope.

nodes.name: chloroplast inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the chloroplast envelope; also faces the chloroplast stroma.

nodes.name: chloroplast outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the chloroplast envelope.

nodes.name: amyloplast membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround an amyloplast and form the amyloplast envelope.

nodes.name: amyloplast inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the amyloplast envelope; also faces the amyloplast stroma.

nodes.name: cyanelle membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround a cyanelle and form the cyanelle envelope.

nodes.name: cyanelle inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the cyanelle envelope; also faces the cyanelle stroma.

nodes.name: cyanelle outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the cyanelle envelope.

nodes.name: etioplast membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround a etioplast and form the etioplast envelope.

nodes.name: chromoplast membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround a chromoplast and form the chromoplast envelope.

nodes.name: chromoplast inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the chromoplast envelope; also faces the chromoplast stroma.

nodes.name: chromoplast outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the chromoplast envelope.

nodes.name: plastid thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer membrane of any thylakoid within a plastid.

nodes.name: chloroplast thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The pigmented membrane of a chloroplast thylakoid. An example of this component is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

nodes.name: cyanelle thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer membrane of any thylakoid within a cyanelle.

nodes.name: prothylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The membrane of prothylakoids, underdeveloped thylakoids found in etioplasts, lacking competent photosynthetic membranes.

nodes.name: photoreceptor disc membrane
nodes.description: Stack of disc membranes located inside a photoreceptor outer segment, and containing densely packed molecules of photoreceptor proteins that traverse the lipid bilayer. Disc membranes arise as evaginations of the ciliary membrane during the development of the outer segment and may or may not remain contiguous with the ciliary membrane.

nodes.name: cone photoreceptor disc membrane
nodes.description: Stack of disc membranes located inside a cone photoreceptor outer segment, and containing densely packed molecules of opsin photoreceptor proteins that traverse the lipid bilayer. Cone disc membranes arise as evaginations of the ciliary membrane during the development of the cone outer segment and remain contiguous with the ciliary membrane.

nodes.name: rod photoreceptor disc membrane
nodes.description: Stack of disc membranes located inside a rod photoreceptor outer segment, and containing densely packed molecules of rhodopsin photoreceptor proteins that traverse the lipid bilayer. It is thought that rod disc membranes arise as evaginations of the ciliary membrane near the base of the outer segment, which then become completely separated from the ciliary membrane, during the development of the rod outer segment.

nodes.name: bounding membrane of organelle
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer that forms the outer-most layer of an organelle.

nodes.name: Golgi membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the compartments of the Golgi apparatus.

nodes.name: vacuolar membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the vacuole and separating its contents from the cytoplasm of the cell.

nodes.name: autophagosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an autophagosome, a double-membrane-bounded vesicle in which endogenous cellular material is sequestered.

nodes.name: amphisome membrane
nodes.description: Any membrane that is part of an amphisome.

nodes.name: autolysosome membrane
nodes.description: A lipid bilayer that surrounds an autolysosome, a single-membrane-bounded vesicle in which endogenous cellular material is degraded.

nodes.name: plant-type vacuole membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vacuole that retains the same shape regardless of cell cycle phase. The membrane separates its contents from the cytoplasm of the cell. An example of this component is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

nodes.name: protein storage vacuole membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a protein storage vacuole.

nodes.name: contractile vacuolar membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the contractile vacuole.

nodes.name: lytic vacuole membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a lytic vacuole and separating its contents from the cytoplasm of the cell.

nodes.name: fungal-type vacuole membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vacuole, the shape of which correlates with cell cycle phase. The membrane separates its contents from the cytoplasm of the cell. An example of this structure is found in Saccharomyces cerevisiae.

nodes.name: lysosomal membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the lysosome and separating its contents from the cell cytoplasm.

nodes.name: azurophil granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an azurophil granule, a primary lysosomal granule found in neutrophil granulocytes that contains a wide range of hydrolytic enzymes and is released into the extracellular fluid.

nodes.name: endolysosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an endolysosome. An endolysosome is a transient hybrid organelle formed by fusion of a late endosome with a lysosome.

nodes.name: phagolysosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a phagolysosome.

nodes.name: cytolytic granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the cytolytic granule.

nodes.name: autolysosome membrane
nodes.description: A lipid bilayer that surrounds an autolysosome, a single-membrane-bounded vesicle in which endogenous cellular material is degraded.

nodes.name: endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an endosome.

nodes.name: early endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an early endosome.

nodes.name: postsynaptic early endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a postsynaptic early endosome.

nodes.name: late endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a late endosome.

nodes.name: multivesicular body membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a multivesicular body.

nodes.name: endolysosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an endolysosome. An endolysosome is a transient hybrid organelle formed by fusion of a late endosome with a lysosome.

nodes.name: recycling endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a recycling endosome.

nodes.name: postsynaptic endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a postsynaptic endosome.

nodes.name: postsynaptic early endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a postsynaptic early endosome.

nodes.name: postsynaptic recycling endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a postsynaptic recycling endosome.

nodes.name: presynaptic endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a presynaptic endosome.

nodes.name: macropinosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a macropinosome.

nodes.name: transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a transport vesicle.

nodes.name: ER to Golgi transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances from the endoplasmic reticulum to the Golgi.

nodes.name: Golgi to ER transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances from the Golgi to the ER.

nodes.name: inter-Golgi transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances within the Golgi.

nodes.name: trans-Golgi network transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances between the trans-Golgi network and other parts of the cell.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted acetylcholine transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted acetylcholine transport vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted glutamate transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted glutamate transport vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted monoamine transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted monoamine transport vesicle.

nodes.name: exocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an exocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: synaptic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a synaptic vesicle.

nodes.name: Golgi-associated vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle associated with the Golgi apparatus.

nodes.name: trans-Golgi network transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances between the trans-Golgi network and other parts of the cell.

nodes.name: COPI-coated vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a COPI-coated vesicle.

nodes.name: Golgi to ER transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances from the Golgi to the ER.

nodes.name: inter-Golgi transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances within the Golgi.

nodes.name: chitosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a chitosome.

nodes.name: coated vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a coated vesicle.

nodes.name: ER to Golgi transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances from the endoplasmic reticulum to the Golgi.

nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances from the Golgi to the ER.

nodes.name: inter-Golgi transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances within the Golgi.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated vesicle.

nodes.name: trans-Golgi network transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle transporting substances between the trans-Golgi network and other parts of the cell.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated endocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated endocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted acetylcholine transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted acetylcholine transport vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted glutamate transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted glutamate transport vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-sculpted monoamine transport vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted monoamine transport vesicle.

nodes.name: endocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an endocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated endocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated endocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: phagocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a phagocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-coated phagocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: early phagosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an early phagosome.

nodes.name: phagolysosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a phagolysosome.

nodes.name: peribacteroid membrane
nodes.description: A membrane that surrounds one or more bacteroids (such as nitrogen-fixing bacteroids within legume root nodule cells).

nodes.name: organellar chromatophore outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, of the two lipid bilayers surrounding an organellar chromatophore.

nodes.name: secretory granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a secretory granule.

nodes.name: acrosomal membrane
nodes.description: The membrane that surrounds the acrosomal lumen. The acrosome is a special type of lysosome in the head of a spermatozoon that contains acid hydrolases and is concerned with the breakdown of the outer membrane of the ovum during fertilization.

nodes.name: platelet dense granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the platelet dense granule.

nodes.name: platelet alpha granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the platelet alpha granule.

nodes.name: dense core granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a dense core granule.

nodes.name: neuronal dense core vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a neuronal dense core vesicle.

nodes.name: azurophil granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an azurophil granule, a primary lysosomal granule found in neutrophil granulocytes that contains a wide range of hydrolytic enzymes and is released into the extracellular fluid.

nodes.name: specific granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a specific granule, a granule with a membranous, tubular internal structure, found primarily in mature neutrophil cells. Most are released into the extracellular fluid. Specific granules contain lactoferrin, lysozyme, vitamin B12 binding protein and elastase.

nodes.name: chromaffin granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a chromaffin granule, a specialized secretory vesicle found in the cells of adrenal glands and various other organs, which is concerned with the synthesis, storage, metabolism, and secretion of epinephrine and norepinephrine.

nodes.name: zymogen granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a zymogen granule.

nodes.name: tertiary granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a tertiary granule.

nodes.name: lamellar body membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a lamellar body. A lamellar body is a membrane-bounded organelle, specialized for the storage and secretion of various substances (surfactant phospholipids, glycoproteins and acid phosphates) which are arranged in the form of tightly packed, concentric, membrane sheets or lamellae. Has some similar properties to, but is distinct from, a lysosome.

nodes.name: alveolar lamellar body membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an alveolar lamellar body, a specialized secretory organelle found in type II pneumocytes and involved in the synthesis, secretion, and reutilization of pulmonary surfactant.

nodes.name: epidermal lamellar body membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an epidermal lamellar body, a specialized secretory organelle found in keratinocytes and involved in the formation of an impermeable, lipid-containing membrane that serves as a water barrier and is required for correct skin barrier function.

nodes.name: ficolin-1-rich granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a ficolin-1-rich granule.

nodes.name: merozoite dense granule membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a dense granule of the type found in apicomplexan parasites.

nodes.name: rough endoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the rough endoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.name: smooth endoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the smooth endoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.name: platelet dense tubular network membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the platelet dense tubular network.

nodes.name: microbody membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a microbody.

nodes.name: peroxisomal membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a peroxisome.

nodes.name: glycosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a glycosome.

nodes.name: glyoxysomal membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a glyoxysome.

nodes.name: organelle outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing in a cellular organelle, lipid bilayer of an organelle envelope.

nodes.name: nuclear outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the nuclear envelope; continuous with the endoplasmic reticulum of the cell and sometimes studded with ribosomes.

nodes.name: mitochondrial outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the mitochondrial envelope.

nodes.name: plastid outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the plastid envelope.

nodes.name: chloroplast outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the chloroplast envelope.

nodes.name: chromoplast outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the chromoplast envelope.

nodes.name: cyanelle outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the cyanelle envelope.

nodes.name: chloroplast thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The pigmented membrane of a chloroplast thylakoid. An example of this component is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

nodes.name: aleurone grain membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an aleurone grain.

nodes.name: sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the sarcoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.name: junctional sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The part of the sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane that contains calcium release channels, is devoted to calcium release and is juxtaposed to transverse tubule membrane. The junctional sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane consists of the junctional region of the terminal cisterna membrane.

nodes.name: free sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The part of the sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane that contains calcium pumps and is devoted to calcium uptake. The free sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane consists of the longitudinal sarcoplasmic reticulum membrane and the non-junctional region of the terminal cisterna membrane.

nodes.name: acidocalcisome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an acidocalcisome.

nodes.name: cis-Golgi network membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the compartments that make up the cis-Golgi network.

nodes.name: attachment organelle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an attachment organelle. This is a region of the cell membrane facing the environment - in mycoplasma, part of the mycolate outer membrane.

nodes.name: endoplasmic reticulum-Golgi intermediate compartment membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the compartments of the endoplasmic reticulum (ER)-Golgi intermediate compartment system.

nodes.name: esterosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding an esterosome. This membrane has characteristics of rough endoplasmic reticulum (RER) membranes.

nodes.name: microneme membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a microneme.

nodes.name: hydrogenosomal membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a hydrogenosome.

nodes.name: ciliary membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a cilium.

nodes.name: ciliary pocket membrane
nodes.description: That part of the plasma membrane found in the ciliary pocket (also called flagellar pocket).

nodes.name: photoreceptor outer segment membrane
nodes.description: The membrane surrounding the outer segment of a vertebrate photoreceptor.

nodes.name: non-motile cilium membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a non-motile cilium.

nodes.name: cone photoreceptor disc membrane
nodes.description: Stack of disc membranes located inside a cone photoreceptor outer segment, and containing densely packed molecules of opsin photoreceptor proteins that traverse the lipid bilayer. Cone disc membranes arise as evaginations of the ciliary membrane during the development of the cone outer segment and remain contiguous with the ciliary membrane.

nodes.name: pigment granule membrane
nodes.description: Any membrane that is part of a pigment granule.

nodes.name: melanosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a melanosome.

nodes.name: multivesicular body, internal vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a multivesicular body internal vesicle.

nodes.name: spine apparatus membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the spine apparatus.

nodes.name: omegasome membrane
nodes.description: Any membrane that is part of an omegasome.

nodes.name: perinuclear endoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The membrane of the perinuclear endoplasmic reticulum, which is the portion of endoplasmic reticulum, the intracellular network of tubules and cisternae, that occurs near the nucleus.

nodes.name: magnetosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a magnetosome.

nodes.name: phagophore assembly site membrane
nodes.description: A cellular membrane associated with the phagophore assembly site.

nodes.name: photosynthetic membrane
nodes.description: A membrane enriched in complexes formed of reaction centers, accessory pigments and electron carriers, in which photosynthetic reactions take place.

nodes.name: thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The pigmented membrane of any thylakoid.

nodes.name: plasma membrane-derived thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The pigmented membrane of a plasma membrane-derived thylakoid.

nodes.name: plastid thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer membrane of any thylakoid within a plastid.

nodes.name: chloroplast thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The pigmented membrane of a chloroplast thylakoid. An example of this component is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

nodes.name: cyanelle thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer membrane of any thylakoid within a cyanelle.

nodes.name: prothylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The membrane of prothylakoids, underdeveloped thylakoids found in etioplasts, lacking competent photosynthetic membranes.

nodes.name: organellar chromatophore thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer membrane of any thylakoid within an organellar chromatophore.

nodes.name: plasma membrane-derived chromatophore membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer associated with a plasma membrane-derived chromatophore; surrounds chromatophores that form complete vesicles.

nodes.name: plasma membrane-derived thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The pigmented membrane of a plasma membrane-derived thylakoid.

nodes.name: ascus membrane
nodes.description: A double layer of lipid molecules that surrounds an ascus, a capsule containing the sexual spores in some fungi.

nodes.name: nuclear outer membrane-endoplasmic reticulum membrane network
nodes.description: The continuous network of membranes encompassing the nuclear outer membrane and the endoplasmic reticulum membrane.

nodes.name: coated membrane
nodes.description: A single or double lipid bilayer with any of several different proteinaceous coats that can associate with membranes. Membrane coats include those formed by clathrin plus an adaptor complex, the COPI and COPII complexes.

nodes.name: prospore membrane leading edge
nodes.description: The region of the prospore membrane that extends to surround the spore nucleus; coated with specific proteins that are thought to play a role in prospore membrane organization.

nodes.name: plasma membrane region
nodes.description: A membrane that is a (regional) part of the plasma membrane.

nodes.name: clathrin-coated pit
nodes.description: A part of the endomembrane system in the form of an invagination of a membrane upon which a clathrin coat forms, and that can be converted by vesicle budding into a clathrin-coated vesicle. Coated pits form on the plasma membrane, where they are involved in receptor-mediated selective transport of many proteins and other macromolecules across the cell membrane, in the trans-Golgi network, and on some endosomes.

nodes.name: basal plasma membrane
nodes.description: The region of the plasma membrane located at the basal end of the cell. Often used in reference to animal polarized epithelial membranes, where the basal membrane is the part attached to the extracellular matrix, or in plant cells, where the basal membrane is defined with respect to the zygotic axis.

nodes.name: basolateral plasma membrane
nodes.description: The region of the plasma membrane that includes the basal end and sides of the cell. Often used in reference to animal polarized epithelial membranes, where the basal membrane is the part attached to the extracellular matrix, or in plant cells, where the basal membrane is defined with respect to the zygotic axis.

nodes.name: apical plasma membrane
nodes.description: The region of the plasma membrane located at the apical end of the cell.

nodes.name: apicolateral plasma membrane
nodes.description: The apical end of the lateral plasma membrane of epithelial cells.

nodes.name: cell projection membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a plasma membrane bounded cell surface projection.

nodes.name: lamellipodium membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a lamellipodium.

nodes.name: uropod membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a uropod.

nodes.name: pseudopodium membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a pseudopodium.

nodes.name: brush border membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding the brush border.

nodes.name: filopodium membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a filopodium.

nodes.name: microvillus membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a microvillus.

nodes.name: rhabdomere microvillus membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a microvillus of a rhabdomere.

nodes.name: ruffle membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a ruffle.

nodes.name: neuron projection membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a neuron projection.

nodes.name: axolemma
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding an axon; it is a specialized trilaminar random mosaic of protein molecules floating within a fluid matrix of highly mobile phospholipid molecules, 7-8 nm in thickness.

nodes.name: dendrite membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a dendrite.

nodes.name: dendritic spine membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a dendritic spine.

nodes.name: stereocilium membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a stereocilium.

nodes.name: rhabdomere membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding the rhabdomere.

nodes.name: muscle cell projection membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a muscle cell projection.

nodes.name: ciliary membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a cilium.

nodes.name: ciliary pocket membrane
nodes.description: That part of the plasma membrane found in the ciliary pocket (also called flagellar pocket).

nodes.name: photoreceptor outer segment membrane
nodes.description: The membrane surrounding the outer segment of a vertebrate photoreceptor.

nodes.name: non-motile cilium membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a non-motile cilium.

nodes.name: cone photoreceptor disc membrane
nodes.description: Stack of disc membranes located inside a cone photoreceptor outer segment, and containing densely packed molecules of opsin photoreceptor proteins that traverse the lipid bilayer. Cone disc membranes arise as evaginations of the ciliary membrane during the development of the cone outer segment and remain contiguous with the ciliary membrane.

nodes.name: mating projection membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a mating projection, the projection formed by unicellular fungi in response to mating pheromone.

nodes.name: macropinocytic cup membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a macropinocytic cup.

nodes.name: plasma membrane of cell tip
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding the cell tip.

nodes.name: mating projection tip membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a mating projection tip.

nodes.name: plasma membrane of growing cell tip
nodes.description: Any plasma membrane part that is part of a growing cell tip.

nodes.name: plasma membrane-derived thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The pigmented membrane of a plasma membrane-derived thylakoid.

nodes.name: cleavage furrow
nodes.description: The cleavage furrow is a plasma membrane invagination at the cell division site. The cleavage furrow begins as a shallow groove and eventually deepens to divide the cytoplasm.

nodes.name: plasma membrane raft
nodes.description: A membrane raft that is part of the plasma membrane.

nodes.name: caveola
nodes.description: A membrane raft that forms small pit, depression, or invagination that communicates with the outside of a cell and extends inward, indenting the cytoplasm and the cell membrane. Examples include flask-shaped invaginations of the plasma membrane in adipocytes associated with caveolin proteins, and minute pits or incuppings of the cell membrane formed during pinocytosis. Caveolae may be pinched off to form free vesicles within the cytoplasm.

nodes.name: eisosome membrane domain/MCC
nodes.description: A plasma membrane part that is composed of a furrow-like plasma membrane domain and associated integral transmembrane proteins.

nodes.name: photoreceptor inner segment membrane
nodes.description: The membrane surrounding the inner segment of a vertebrate photoreceptor. The photoreceptor inner segment contains mitochondria, ribosomes and membranes where opsin molecules are assembled and passed to be part of the outer segment discs.

nodes.name: synaptic membrane
nodes.description: A specialized area of membrane on either the presynaptic or the postsynaptic side of a synapse, the junction between a nerve fiber of one neuron and another neuron or muscle fiber or glial cell.

nodes.name: dendritic spine membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a dendritic spine.

nodes.name: presynaptic periactive zone
nodes.description: A region that surrounds the active zone of the presynaptic plasma membrane, and is specialized for the control of synaptic development.

nodes.name: presynaptic membrane
nodes.description: A specialized area of membrane of the axon terminal that faces the plasma membrane of the neuron or muscle fiber with which the axon terminal establishes a synaptic junction; many synaptic junctions exhibit structural presynaptic characteristics, such as conical, electron-dense internal protrusions, that distinguish it from the remainder of the axon plasma membrane.

nodes.name: postsynaptic membrane
nodes.description: A specialized area of membrane facing the presynaptic membrane on the tip of the nerve ending and separated from it by a minute cleft (the synaptic cleft). Neurotransmitters cross the synaptic cleft and transmit the signal to the postsynaptic membrane.

nodes.name: presynaptic active zone membrane
nodes.description: The membrane portion of the presynaptic active zone; it is the site where docking and fusion of synaptic vesicles occurs for the release of neurotransmitters.

nodes.name: presynaptic endocytic zone membrane
nodes.description: The region of the presynaptic membrane that is part of the presynaptic endocytic zone - where synaptic vesicles are endocytosed and recycled following release.

nodes.name: postsynaptic endocytic zone membrane
nodes.description: The region of the postsynaptic membrane that is part of the postsynaptic endocytic zone. This region of membrane is associated with stable clathrin puncta.

nodes.name: postsynaptic specialization membrane
nodes.description: The membrane component of the postsynaptic specialization. This is the region of the postsynaptic membrane in which the population of neurotransmitter receptors involved in synaptic transmission are concentrated.

nodes.name: postsynaptic density membrane
nodes.description: The membrane component of the postsynaptic density. This is the region of the postsynaptic membrane in which the population of neurotransmitter receptors involved in synaptic transmission are concentrated.

nodes.name: postsynaptic specialization membrane of symmetric synapse
nodes.description: The membrane component of the postsynaptic specialization of a symmetic synapse. This is the region of the postsynaptic membrane in which the population of neurotransmitter receptors involved in synaptic transmission are concentrated.

nodes.name: caveola neck
nodes.description: A membrane microdomain that forms a necklace around the bulb (crater) of a caveola. Intramembrane particles are concentrated in this region and cytoskeletal components, including actin, are highly enriched in the area underlying it.

nodes.name: cellularization cleavage furrow
nodes.description: A plasma membrane invagination at the site of separation of a multi-nucleate cell or syncytium into individual cells.

nodes.name: apical plasma membrane urothelial plaque
nodes.description: A scallop-shaped plaque, also referred to as an asymmetric unit membrane (AUM), found in the apical plasma membrane of urothelial superficial (umbrella) cells which form a a barrier to the passage of water and soluble toxic compounds found in urine. The plaques are thickened regions of membrane composed of uroplakin transmembrane proteins which form a crystalline array.

nodes.name: hinge region between urothelial plaques of apical plasma membrane
nodes.description: A narrow rim of non-thickened membrane in between urothelial plaques in apical plasma membrane.

nodes.name: periciliary membrane compartment
nodes.description: A plasma membrane region adjacent to the base of eukaryotic cilia and flagella that is enriched in endocytosis-associated proteins and vesicles and that appears to regulate ciliary membrane homeostasis.

nodes.name: sperm head plasma membrane
nodes.description: The plasma membrane that is part of the head section of a sperm cell.

nodes.name: pellicular membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding the pellicle, a structure enclosing some parasite cells such as certain apicomplexa and Euglenozoa. These membranes are associated with an infrastructure of microtubules, microfilaments, and other organelles.

nodes.name: membrane microdomain
nodes.description: A membrane region with a lipid composition that is distinct from that of the membrane regions that surround it.

nodes.name: membrane raft
nodes.description: Any of the small (10-200 nm), heterogeneous, highly dynamic, sterol- and sphingolipid-enriched membrane domains that compartmentalize cellular processes. Small rafts can sometimes be stabilized to form larger platforms through protein-protein and protein-lipid interactions.

nodes.name: plasma membrane raft
nodes.description: A membrane raft that is part of the plasma membrane.

nodes.name: caveola
nodes.description: A membrane raft that forms small pit, depression, or invagination that communicates with the outside of a cell and extends inward, indenting the cytoplasm and the cell membrane. Examples include flask-shaped invaginations of the plasma membrane in adipocytes associated with caveolin proteins, and minute pits or incuppings of the cell membrane formed during pinocytosis. Caveolae may be pinched off to form free vesicles within the cytoplasm.

nodes.name: eisosome membrane domain/MCC
nodes.description: A plasma membrane part that is composed of a furrow-like plasma membrane domain and associated integral transmembrane proteins.

nodes.name: caveola neck
nodes.description: A membrane microdomain that forms a necklace around the bulb (crater) of a caveola. Intramembrane particles are concentrated in this region and cytoskeletal components, including actin, are highly enriched in the area underlying it.

nodes.name: caveola bulb
nodes.description: The region of a caveola that extends into the cytoplasm, excluding the neck (rim). This region is associated with intracellular caveola proteins.

nodes.name: pathogen-containing vacuole membrane
nodes.description: Host-derived membrane of a pathogen-containing vacuole.

nodes.name: spore inner membrane
nodes.description: The membrane surrounding the spore core (endospore core) that separates it from its external environment.

nodes.name: lateral plasma membrane
nodes.description: The portion of the plasma membrane at the lateral side of the cell. In epithelial cells, lateral plasma membranes are on the sides of cells which lie at the interface of adjacent cells.

nodes.name: nuclear matrix
nodes.description: The dense fibrillar network lying on the inner side of the nuclear membrane.

nodes.name: nuclear body
nodes.description: Extra-nucleolar nuclear domains usually visualized by confocal microscopy and fluorescent antibodies to specific proteins.

nodes.name: nuclear dicing body
nodes.description: A small round nuclear body, measuring 0.2-0.8 microns in diameter that is diffusely distributed throughout the nucleoplasm. Several proteins known to be involved in miRNA processing have been localized to these structures. D-bodies are thought to be involved in primary-miRNA processing and/or storage/assembly of miRNA processing complexes.

nodes.name: Cajal body
nodes.description: A class of nuclear body, first seen after silver staining by Ramon y Cajal in 1903, enriched in small nuclear ribonucleoproteins, and certain general RNA polymerase II transcription factors; ultrastructurally, they appear as a tangle of coiled, electron-dense threads roughly 0.5 micrometers in diameter; involved in aspects of snRNP biogenesis; the protein coilin serves as a marker for Cajal bodies. Some argue that Cajal bodies are the sites for preassembly of transcriptosomes, unitary particles involved in transcription and processing of RNA.

nodes.name: PML body
nodes.description: A class of nuclear body; they react against SP100 auto-antibodies (PML, promyelocytic leukemia); cells typically contain 10-30 PML bodies per nucleus; alterations in the localization of PML bodies occurs after viral infection.

nodes.name: LYSP100-associated nuclear domain
nodes.description: A nuclear body that is enriched in the lymphoid cell-specific protein LYSp100B; LANDs are globular, electron-dense structures and are morphologically distinct from the annular structures characteristic of PML bodies.

nodes.name: nuclear speck
nodes.description: A discrete extra-nucleolar subnuclear domain, 20-50 in number, in which splicing factors are seen to be localized by immunofluorescence microscopy.

nodes.name: omega speckle
nodes.description: A nucleoplasmic speckle distributed in the interchromatin space of cells in close proximity to chromatin. Omega speckles are distinct from interchromatin granules and contain heterogeneous nuclear RNA-binding proteins (hnRNPs).

nodes.name: interchromatin granule
nodes.description: A class of nuclear body measuring 20-25 nm in diameter and distributed throughout the interchromatin space, linked together by thin fibrils. They are believed to be storage centers for various snRNAs, snRNPs, serine/arginine-rich proteins and RNA polymerase II. A typical mammalian cell contains 25-50 clusters of interchromatin granules. Interchromatin granule clusters do not contain the heterogeneous nuclear RNA-binding proteins (hnRNPs).

nodes.name: histone locus body
nodes.description: A nuclear body associated with the histone gene locus that is thought to contain all of the factors necessary for histone mRNA transcription and pre-mRNA processing. In Drosophila, U7 snRNP is located in the histone locus body rather than the distinct Cajal body.

nodes.name: paraspeckles
nodes.description: Discrete subnuclear bodies in the interchromatin nucleoplasmic space, often located adjacent to nuclear specks. 10-20 paraspeckles are typically found in human cell nuclei.

nodes.name: sphere organelle
nodes.description: A nuclear body that is found in the germinal vesicles of amphibian oocytes, and consist of three major parts: a remarkably spherical body about 5-10 pm in diameter, smaller spherical or nearly spherical granules on the surface, and inclusions of various sizes that strongly resemble the surface granules. The parts of the sphere organelle have distinct compositions, including splicing snRNAs and proteins.

nodes.name: cleavage body
nodes.description: A nuclear body that contains proteins involved in pre-mRNA 3'-end cleavage and polyadenylation, such as DDX1, CSTF2 and CPSFs, as well as the transcription factors TFIIE and TFIIF. Cleavage bodies are localized adjacent to Cajal bodies and are involved in mRNA3'-end processing.

nodes.name: Gemini of coiled bodies
nodes.description: Nuclear bodies frequently found near or associated with Cajal bodies (also called coiled bodies or CBs). Gemini of coiled bodies, or 'gems', are similar in size and shape to CBs, and often indistinguishable under the microscope. Unlike CBs, gems do not contain small nuclear ribonucleoproteins (snRNPs); they contain a protein called survivor of motor neurons (SMN) whose function relates to snRNP biogenesis. Gems are believed to assist CBs in snRNP biogenesis, and to play a role in the etiology of spinal muscular atrophy (SMA).

nodes.name: nuclear exosome focus
nodes.description: An nuclear body involved in nuclear mRNA surveilllance. Contains at least Mmi1, or an ortholog of it, and the nuclear exosome.

nodes.name: host cellular component
nodes.description: Any cellular component of a host cell. The host is an organism in which another organism, for instance a parasite or symbiont, spends part or all of its life cycle and from which it obtains nourishment and/or protection.

nodes.name: host cell part
nodes.description: Any constituent part of a host cell. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: symbiont-containing vacuolar space
nodes.description: The space between a symbiont plasma membrane and the symbiont-containing vacuole membrane.

nodes.name: symbiont-containing vacuole membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a symbiont-containing vacuole, derived from both the host and symbiont.

nodes.name: symbiont-containing vacuolar membrane network
nodes.description: Tubular network of extensions from the symbiont-containing vacuole membrane that protrude into the host cytoplasm.

nodes.name: host cell membrane
nodes.description: Double layer of lipid molecules as it encloses host cells, and, in eukaryotes, many organelles; may be a single or double lipid bilayer; also includes associated proteins. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host cell plasma membrane
nodes.description: The plasma membrane surrounding a host cell.

nodes.name: host cell endomembrane system
nodes.description: A collection of membranous structures involved in transport within the host cell. The main components of the endomembrane system are endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi bodies, vesicles, cell membrane and nuclear envelope. Members of the endomembrane system pass materials through each other or though the use of vesicles. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: The pigmented membrane of any host thylakoid.

nodes.name: host cell chloroplast thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: Any sac-like membranous structures (cisternae) in a chloroplast found in host cells, combined into stacks (grana) and present singly in the stroma (stroma thylakoids or frets) as interconnections between grana. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host cell cytoplasmic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a host cell cytoplasmic vesicle.

nodes.name: host cell endocytic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a host cell endocytic vesicle.

nodes.name: host cell synaptic vesicle membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a host synaptic vesicle.

nodes.name: double membrane vesicle viral factory membrane
nodes.description: One of the two endoplasmic reticulum-derived lipid bilayer membranes that bound a double membrane vesicle viral factory.

nodes.name: double membrane vesicle viral factory inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner of the two endoplasmic reticulum-derived lipid bilayer membranes that bound a double membrane vesicle viral factory.

nodes.name: double membrane vesicle viral factory outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer of the two endoplasmic reticulum-derived lipid bilayer membranes that bound a double membrane vesicle viral factory.

nodes.name: host cell endoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the host cell endoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.name: host cell rough endoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the host cell rough endoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.name: host cell smooth endoplasmic reticulum membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the host cell smooth endoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.name: host cell endoplasmic reticulum-Golgi intermediate compartment membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the compartments of the host cell ER-Golgi intermediate compartment system.

nodes.name: host cell endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a host cell endosome.

nodes.name: host cell late endosome membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding a host cell late endosome.

nodes.name: host cell Golgi membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the compartments of the host cell Golgi apparatus.

nodes.name: host cell lysosomal membrane
nodes.description: The lipid bilayer surrounding the host cell lysosome and separating its contents from the host cell cytoplasm.

nodes.name: host cell mitochondrial membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround the host cell mitochondrion and form the host cell mitochondrial envelope.

nodes.name: host cell mitochondrial inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the host cell mitochondrial envelope. It is highly folded to form cristae.

nodes.name: host cell mitochondrial outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the host cell mitochondrial envelope.

nodes.name: host cell nuclear membrane
nodes.description: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround the host nucleus and form the nuclear envelope; excludes the intermembrane space.

nodes.name: host cell nuclear inner membrane
nodes.description: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the host nuclear envelope.

nodes.name: host cell nuclear outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the host nuclear envelope; continuous with the endoplasmic reticulum of the host cell and sometimes studded with ribosomes.

nodes.name: host outer membrane
nodes.description: The external membrane of Gram-negative bacteria or certain organelles such as mitochondria and chloroplasts; freely permeable to most ions and metabolites, occurring in a host cell.

nodes.name: host organelle outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing in a cellular organelle, lipid bilayer of an organelle envelope, occurring in a host cell.

nodes.name: host cell mitochondrial outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the host cell mitochondrial envelope.

nodes.name: host cell nuclear outer membrane
nodes.description: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the host nuclear envelope; continuous with the endoplasmic reticulum of the host cell and sometimes studded with ribosomes.

nodes.name: host cell outer membrane
nodes.description: A lipid bilayer that forms the outermost layer of the cell envelope, occurring in a host cell.

nodes.name: extrahaustorial membrane
nodes.description: The membrane surrounding the symbiont haustorium during symbiosis, derived from the host plasma membrane.

nodes.name: hyphal membrane
nodes.description: A host-derived membrane surrounding the symbiont hypha during infection.

nodes.name: periarbuscular membrane
nodes.description: A host-derived membrane surrounding the symbiont arbuscule during symbiosis.

nodes.name: host intracellular part
nodes.description: Any constituent part of the living contents of a host cell; the matter contained within (but not including) the plasma membrane, usually taken to exclude large vacuoles and masses of secretory or ingested material. In eukaryotes it includes the nucleus and cytoplasm. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host cell cytoplasm
nodes.description: The cytoplasm of a host cell.

nodes.name: host intracellular organelle
nodes.description: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, occurring within the host cell. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton. Excludes the plasma membrane. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host intracellular membrane-bounded organelle
nodes.description: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, as found in host cells, bounded by a single or double lipid bilayer membrane and occurring within the cell. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, and vesicles. Excludes the plasma membrane. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host cell mitochondrion
nodes.description: A semiautonomous, self replicating organelle as found in host cells that occurs in varying numbers, shapes, and sizes in the cell cytoplasm. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host cell plastid
nodes.description: Any member of a family of organelles as found in the cytoplasm of host cells, which are membrane-bounded and contain DNA. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host cell chloroplast
nodes.description: A chlorophyll-containing plastid as found within host cells with thylakoids organized into grana and frets, or stroma thylakoids, and embedded in a stroma. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host cell chloroplast part
nodes.description: Any constituent part of a chloroplast as it is found in host cells and which are a chlorophyll-containing plastid with thylakoids organized into grana and frets, or stroma thylakoids, and embedded in a stroma. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host cell chloroplast thylakoid membrane
nodes.description: Any sac-like membranous structures (cisternae) in a chloroplast found in host cells, combined into stacks (grana) and present singly in the stroma (stroma thylakoids or frets) as interconnections between grana. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host cell nucleus
nodes.description: A membrane-bounded organelle as it is found in the host cell in which chromosomes are housed and replicated. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.name: host symbiosome
nodes.description: A double-enveloped cell compartment, composed of the endosymbiont with its plasmalemma (as inner envelope) and an outer envelope (the perisymbiontic membrane) derived from the host cell.

nodes.name: host bacteroid-containing symbiosome
nodes.description: A symbiosome containing any of various structurally modified bacteria, such as those occurring on the root nodules of leguminous plants, of a host cell.

nodes.name: host cell cytoplasmic vesicle
nodes.description: A vesicle formed of membrane or protein, found in the cytoplasm of a host cell.

nodes.name: host cell synaptic vesicle
nodes.description: A secretory organelle of a host cell, some 50 nm in diameter, of presynaptic nerve terminals; accumulates in high concentrations of neurotransmitters and secretes these into the synaptic cleft by fusion with the 'active zone' of the presynaptic plasma membrane.

nodes.name: host cell endoplasmic reticulum
nodes.description: The irregular network of unit membranes, visible only by electron microscopy, that occurs in the host cell cytoplasm of many eukaryotic cells. The membranes form a complex meshwork of tubular channels, which are often expanded into slitlike cavities called cisternae. The host ER takes two forms, rough (or granular), with ribosomes adhering to the outer surface, and smooth (with no ribosomes attached).

nodes.name: host cell rough endoplasmic reticulum
nodes.description: The irregular network of unit membranes, visible only by electron microscopy, that occurs in the host cell cytoplasm of many eukaryotic cells. The membranes form a complex meshwork of tubular channels, which are often expanded into slitlike cavities called cisternae. The host rough ER has ribosomes adhering to the outer surface.

nodes.name: host cell smooth endoplasmic reticulum
nodes.description: The irregular network of unit membranes, visible only by electron microscopy, that occurs in the host cell cytoplasm of many eukaryotic cells. The membranes form a complex meshwork of tubular channels, which are often expanded into slitlike cavities called cisternae. The host smooth ER has no ribosomes adhering to the outer surface.

nodes.name: host cell endoplasmic reticulum-Golgi intermediate compartment
nodes.description: A complex system of membrane-bounded compartments located between host cell endoplasmic reticulum (ER) and the host Golgi complex, with a distinctive membrane protein composition; involved in ER-to-Golgi transport.

nodes.name: host cell endosome
nodes.description: A membrane-bounded organelle that carries materials newly ingested by endocytosis. It passes many of the materials to host cell lysosomes for degradation.

nodes.name: host cell late endosome
nodes.description: A prelysosomal endocytic organelle differentiated from host early endosomes by lower lumenal pH and different protein composition. Host late endosomes are more spherical than early endosomes and are mostly juxtanuclear, being concentrated near the microtubule organizing center.

nodes.name: host multivesicular body
nodes.description: A late endosome in which regions of the limiting host cell endosomal membrane invaginate to form internal vesicles; host membrane proteins that enter the internal vesicles are sequestered from the host cytoplasm.

nodes.name: host cell lysosome
nodes.description: A small lytic vacuole that has cell cycle-independent morphology and is found in most host animal cells and that contains a variety of hydrolases, most of which have their maximal activities in the pH range 5-6. The contained enzymes display latency if properly isolated. About 40 different lysosomal hydrolases are known and host cell lysosomes have a great variety of morphologies and functions.

nodes.name: host cell viral assembly compartment
nodes.description: A membrane-bounded compartment that forms in the cytoplasm of the host cell, in which virus assembly takes place.

nodes.name: host cell peroxisome
nodes.description: A small host cell organelle enclosed by a single membrane, and found in most eukaryotic cells. Contains peroxidases and other enzymes involved in a variety of metabolic processes including free radical detoxification, lipid catabolism and biosynthesis, and hydrogen peroxide metabolism.

nodes.name: host thylakoid
nodes.description: A membranous cellular structure within the host cell that bears the photosynthetic pigments in plants, algae, and cyanobacteria. In cyanobacteria thylakoids are of various shapes and are attached to, or continuous with, the host plasma membrane. In eukaryotic host cells they are flattened, membrane-bounded disk-like structures located in the chloroplasts; in the chloroplasts of higher plants the thylakoids form dense stacks called grana. Isolated thylakoid preparations can carry out photosynthetic electron transport and the associated phosphorylation.

nodes.name: host cytoskeleton
nodes.description: A cellular structure that forms the internal framework of eukaryotic and prokaryotic host cells. The cytoskeleton includes intermediate filaments, microfilaments, microtubules, the microtrabecular lattice, and other structures characterized by a polymeric filamentous nature and long-range order within the cell. The various elements of the cytoskeleton not only serve in the maintenance of cellular shape but also have roles in other cellular functions, including cellular movement, cell division, endocytosis, and movement of organelles.

nodes.name: host cell centrosome
nodes.description: A structure in a host cell comprised of a core structure (in most organisms, a pair of centrioles) and peripheral material from which a microtubule-based structure, such as a spindle apparatus, is organized. Centrosomes occur close to the nucleus during interphase in many eukaryotic cells, though in animal cells it changes continually during the cell-division cycle.

nodes.name: host chromosome
nodes.description: A structure composed of a very long molecule of DNA and associated proteins (e.g. histones) that carries hereditary information, occurring within a host cell.

nodes.name: host cell cytoplasm part
